  <summary>8/2/2001--Introduced.
School Safety Enhancement and Website Protection Act of 2001 - Amends Federal criminal law to apply specified criminal penalties for fraud and related activity in connection with computers to: (1) unauthorized access to information on websites of elementary and secondary schools and institutions of higher education; and (2) threats to public health or safety.</summary>
